# Figma-first design workflow

For all UI/frontend work on ExpenseKit, follow this order. Do not implement visual changes until design is approved.

## Phase 1 — Design (Figma)

1. Create or update designs in Figma before writing UI code.
2. Deliverables per screen/feature:
   - Figma file link (view access for review)
   - Pages: Mobile (375px) + Desktop (1440px) at minimum
   - Components: buttons, inputs, cards, nav, typography scale, color tokens
   - States: default, hover, empty, loading, error
3. If direct Figma editing is unavailable, provide a **Figma-ready spec** (frames, spacing, colors, copy) the user can paste into Figma, or reference mockups for approval.

## Phase 2 — Approval (user gate)

- Stop and wait for explicit user approval (e.g. "approved", "go ahead", "implement").
- Do not implement layout, colors, or new screens until approved.
- Revisions stay in Figma/spec until re-approved.

## Phase 3 — Implementation (code)

1. Match Figma: spacing, typography, colors, border-radius, shadows.
2. Extract tokens into Tailwind theme or CSS variables when practical.
3. Reuse components; avoid one-off styles that diverge from the design system.
4. After build, note any intentional deviations from Figma.

## Figma handoff checklist

- [ ] Figma link shared
- [ ] User approved design
- [ ] Colors/fonts/spacing documented
- [ ] Mobile + desktop covered
- [ ] Empty and error states included
